@node Cap02E "INTRODUCING MaPuS:"


What  is  MaPuS?  MaPuS is the ultimate solution for DMS files.  You can do
all  you  want  on  these  files.  You can check them, make, remove and add
tail, track, front banners; all in a good and functional way.

@endnode

@node Cap03E "WHY SHOULD YOU USE MaPuS AND NOT ANOTHER CHECKER?"


Simple.   Some  doesn't  work perfectly on all files, others don't give you
all  informations  about the file, and no-one lets you add your text files.
MaPuS can be used with a @{"BBS" Link AXusoE} or into your @{"script files"
Link  Cap05E} or simply to @{"check" Link Cap04E}
your DMS files.  MaPuS is 100% tested for these functions.

@endnode

@node Cap04E "HOW DOES IT WORK:"

If you invoke MaPuS with only his name, you'll get the syntax:

MaPuS [-<options>] FileName[.DMS] [DestFile]

Options:

@{" Operations on front banners " Link FrontOptE}
@{" Operations on track banners " Link TrackOptE}
@{" Operations on tail banners " Link TailOptE}
        @{" Other options " Link VarieOptE}


If you invoke MaPuS with the source file name only, the file will be tested
and are printed on the screen many informations about it.

You can also specify wildcards in source file name:  *, ?, #?.

@{b}Please update your MaPuS.cfg on every revision of MaPuS.@{ub}

@endnode

@node FrontOptE "Operations on front banners:"





@{" a " Link OptaE} add a front banner.
@{" r " Link OptrE} remove front banners.
@{" m " Link OptmE} make a front banner.





@endnode

@node TrackOptE "Operations on track banners:"




@{" t " Link OptaE} add a track banner.
@{" k " Link OptrE} remove track banners.
@{" n " Link OptmE} make a track banner.





@endnode

@node TailOptE "Operations on tail banners:"




@{" A " Link OptaE} add a tail banner.
@{" R " Link OptrE} remove tail banners.
@{" M " Link OptmE} make a tail banner.




@endnode

@node OptaE "Add a banner:"


Specify  source  "FileName"  (with  or  without .DMS extention) and, if you
want, a destination file "DestFile".

MaPuS  will  test  that  file  and  add  the  banner to the destination one
(making,  so,  a  copy  of  the  source  file) or if the destination is not
specified to the source file directly.

If the source file name were absent, an ARP requester would appear.

@{b}NOTE:@{ub} If you want to create the destination file in RAM: use the @{"s" Link VarieOptE} option.

"FileName"  can  be  without  extention,  but  you MUST write the extention
yourself in the destination file name.

@endnode

@node OptrE "Remove banners:"

Pass  source FileName and/or DestFile name and MaPuS will search and remove
front  banners and report to you operation results.  If no destination file
were specified, the banners would be stripped to the source file directly.

If you don't specify FileName, an ARP requester will appear.

@{b}NOTE:@{ub} If you use the RAM: specify the @{"s" Link VarieOpt} option.

@endnode

@node OptmE "Create banners:"


Pass  the  text  file  name  or a requester will appear and it will let you
select  a  filename  as  banner.   MaPuS  will  place in S:  a file, called
"MaPuS.cfg".  Now you can add it to your DMS files.

Text file format is:  64 colums (with linefeed) for 16 lines.


@endnode

@node VarieOptE "Other options:"

@{b} s @{ub}  -  Don't check free space. You should use it if you work with RAM:

@{b} v @{ub}  -  View DMS file informations only, and don't check it.

@{b} d @{ub}  -  Add to track banners the uploading date.

@{b} g @{ub}  -  Show some greetings.

@{b} u @{ub}  -  Use an ARP requester to select the DMS file.

@{b} f @{ub}  -  Show informations about every track of the DMS file.

@{b} c @{ub}  -  Activate return codes. If the checking fails a return code of
        15 will be returned.


@endnode

@node Cap05E "EXAMPLES:"

1) Check a file:
 In this example I will suppose that you've a file in your DL: directory
called TEST.DMS and you want to test it.

Type: MaPuS DL:TEST or MaPuS dl:TEST.dms

it will be tested and you'll get some infos about the file.

2) Make a @{"tail banner" Link TailOptE}:

Type: MaPuS -M

3) Add a @{"front banner" Link FrontOptE} and remove @{"tail" Link TailOptE} and @{"track banners" Link TrackOptE}:

Type: MaPuS -AskR dl:TEST.dms ram:newTEST.dms

(Note @{"s" Link VarieOptE} option for RAM:)

4) Test all files of a directory:

MaPuS dl:*.dms or MaPuS dl:#?.dms

@endnode

Ciao...

@node AXusoE "/X or DLG using:"


If you want to use MaPuS with AmiExpress have a look at: @{b}bbs/fcheck/DMS@{ub}

<----- THERE's THE CONTENTS OF THE FILE ---------- CUT HERE ------------->
MaPuS

Error
<------------------------------------------------- CUT HERE ------------->

NOTE: the 2nd line contains the options for MaPuS.

@{b} REMEMBER: @{ub} The file must contains these 3 lines only!

If you've AmiExpress v3+ place file "DMS.info" into BBS:FCheck directory.

The  scripts  to  use  MaPuS with DLG are included in the archive, and they
are:

DLGConfig/Batch/UPLOAD1.BATCH
DLGConfig/Text/Banner.displayme
DLGConfig/Text/PreDesc.txt

@endnode

@node Cap06E "GLOSSARY:"

@{"Tail Banner" Link TailOptE}: it's a text file that will be appended to the end of file.
             (it's the last text that will be displayed unpacking)

@{"Front Banner" Link FrontOptE}: it's a text file that will be appended to the front of file.
              (it's the first text that will be displayed unpacking)

@{"Track Banner" Link TrackOptE}: it's the zero-track that will displayed as text file.

@endnode

@node Cap07E "MaPuS UPDATES:"

0.** Sperimental versions never released.

0.84 First public version.  For our decision, public versions don't
     implement @{"-k" Link TrackOptE} command.

0.85 First registered version, got if you've called @{"IRON LAW BBS" Link Cap10E}.

0.86-0.91 Private versions.
     Fixed some bugs: Before @{"-k" Link TrackOptE} command corrupted archives if there were
     track and front banner.

0.92 Public version.
     New  option @{"-f" Link VarieOptE}.  If you specify it, MaPuS will show you informations
     about every track.

0.93 Registered version.

0.94 Sperimental version never released.

0.95 Shareware version.
     Fixed a bug in @{"-f" Link VarieOptE} option (the infos were not displayed if the file
     had been selected from requester).

0.96 Shareware version.
     Fixed a bug. Now MaPuS can be resident. Thanks to Felix for bug
     reporting.

0.97 Registered version.

0.98-0.99 Private versions.

1.00 Shareware version, not 100% beacause no one has registered his copy of
     MaPuS! If you want the complete version you must pay the registration
     fee or call @{"IRON LAW BBS" Link Cap10E}.
     Wildcards added (*,?,#?).  Speeded up stripping routine.
     Docs  are  now  also  in Amiga-Guide format, that contains english and
     italian ones. Archive structure modified.

1.01 Registered version.

1.02-1.09 Private versions.

1.10 Special version released at SMAU 1993.  Added the uploading date
     (useful for BBS) on track banners (use @{"-d" Link VarieOptE} option).  Now you can stop
     MaPuS with CTRL-C (after the test).

1.11 Registered version.

1.12 Fixed a problem in @{"-t" Link TrackoptE} option. A bug made 1.10 not working on 68000
     systems.

1.13 Registered version.

1.14 Fixed two problems:
     1) If the filename started with a minus character the command line
        parsing didn't worked.
     2) Sometimes the track banners adding did corrupt the archive.

1.15 Registered version.

1.16 Fixed two bugs:
     1) If CTRL-C was pressed during a file check, the program crashed the
        system.
     2) Small command line bug.
     Now MaPuS informations are compatible with DMS V1.51+.
     Guide corrected, ASCII docs deleted.

1.17 Registered version.

1.18-1.29 Private, not released, versions.
         Note: I saw a "1.20" version. This version hasn't been created by us,
         you shouldn't use it..

1.30 Fixed some bugs: now an empty file checking doesn't do problems.

     Now supporting "": file name can contain spaces, if between "".

1.31 Registered version.

1.32 Added return codes with @{"-c" Link VarieOptE} option. It  returns a code of 15 if the
     checking fails. Signaled by Jay Ruyle.

1.33 Registered version.


@endnode

@node Cap08E "FUTURE FEATURES:"


- MaPuS will take the file list to operate over from a text file.

- Use of a better requester.

- Banner display.

- Scripts for failed or successful tests (useful for BBSes).

- Date adding on tail and front banners.

- MaPuS will select a random banner to add.


@endnode

